        "title": "feat(data): add bounded data run evidence",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add `crabbox data` as a thin wrapper over `crabbox run` for repo-owned data workflows with required bounded manifests.\n- Validate `crabbox.data-run.v1` manifests locally, reject unsafe/unknown proof fields and unproven `enforced` policy claims, write local summaries, and attach bounded `dataSummary` metadata to coordinator run records when available.\n- Add provider-neutral delegated artifact retrieval plus Islo single-file support for `--require-artifact` / `--download`, while keeping globs and unsupported delegated providers fail-closed.\n- Add provider-neutral data-run policy hooks for source identity, sink identity, egress, and promotion declarations. Islo participates as `declared-only`; `enforced` remains reserved for adapters that can prove enforcement.\n- Harden data-run local output containment, Worker broker metadata sanitization, and Islo retrieval against symlink, oversize, unsafe proof-key, and archive-chunk log-leak edge cases.\n\n## Issue Coverage\n| Issue | Status in this PR | Notes |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/225 | Implemented as product framing | Keeps the feature framed as generic run evidence over caller-owned commands and bounded proof. |\n| https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/227 | Implemented for first provider | Adds the provider-neutral delegated artifact capability and proves it on Islo. Other delegated providers remain fail-closed until adapters implement it. |\n| https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/228 | Implemented | Adds bounded manifest validation, local summaries, and coordinator run-record `dataSummary` storage with Worker-side sanitization. |\n| https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/229 | Implemented | Adds the thin `crabbox data run` wrapper over existing run primitives. |\n| https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/230 | Implemented as declaration/hook layer | Adds provider-neutral policy hooks and explicit enforcement tiers. This PR does not claim provider-enforced identity/egress/promotion where an adapter cannot prove it. |\n\n## Test plan\n- `go test ./internal/cli ./internal/providers/islo ./internal/providers/wandb`\n- `go test ./...`\n- `npm test --prefix worker`\n- `npm run check --prefix worker`\n- `npm run lint --prefix worker`\n- `npm run format:check --prefix worker`\n- `scripts/check-docs.sh`\n\n## Fresh Live Islo E2E Proof\nThis was run from PR head `5e83c09`. A short-lived API key was created through `islo api-key create --expires 1`, used only via `CRABBOX_ISLO_API_KEY`, then deleted. Lease/sandbox IDs are redacted.\n\n```text\nISLO_LIVE_HEAD 5e83c09\nISLO_LIVE_STATUS 0\nISLO_LIVE_PROOF_BEGIN\ndata policy source=declared-live-smoke sink=declared-live-smoke egress=provider-default promotion=manual enforcement=declared-only\nleased <redacted> slug=<redacted> provider=islo sandbox=<redacted>\nprovider=islo lease=<redacted> sandbox=<redacted>\nrequired artifact reports/data/manifest.json matched=1\nrequired artifact reports/data/empty.marker matched=1\ndownloaded .crabbox/data-runs/islo-live-proof/manifest.json bytes=189\nislo run summary sync_skipped=true command=433ms total=47.712s exit=0\n{\"provider\":\"islo\",\"leaseId\":\"<redacted>\",\"syncMs\":0,\"syncPhases\":[{\"name\":\"sync\",\"skipped\":true,\"reason\":\"--no-sync\"}],\"syncSkipped\":true,\"syncDelegated\":true,\"commandMs\":433,\"totalMs\":47712,\"exitCode\":0,\"label\":\"data:islo-live-proof\",\"artifacts\":[{\"kind\":\"delegated-download\",\"path\":\".crabbox/data-runs/islo-live-proof/manifest.json\",\"bytes\":189}]}\ndata run islo-live-proof manifest ok status=success inputs=0 outputs=1 summary=.crabbox/data-runs/islo-live-proof/summary.json\nISLO_LIVE_PROOF_END\n```\n\n## Provider Scope\n- Islo is the delegated provider proven live in this PR for bounded single-file required artifacts and downloads.\n- W&B/CoreWeave remains on its existing delegated-run contract and still rejects artifact retrieval flags in this PR.\n- `enforced` data-run policy claims are reserved for adapters that can prove enforcement; this PR supports `declared-only` and `unsupported` and exposes the provider hook for future enforcement-capable adapters.",
